<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2185] add @Deprecated annotations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2185</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;as discussed on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2084&quot; title=&quot;remove Byte/CharBuffer wrapping for collation key generation&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2084&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I think we should be consistent about use of @Deprecated annotations if we are to use it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch adds the missing annotations... unfortunately i cannot commit this for some time, because my internet connection does not support heavy committing (it is difficult to even upload a large patch).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So if someone wants to take it, have fun, otherwise in a week or so I will commit it if nobody objects.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
